Additionally, the crystal violet staining method was also employed to investigate the destructive ability of VOIMBr-CD on the formed S. aureus biofilm. At a concentration of 400 μg/mL, the disruption rate of VOIMBr-CD on the formed S. aureus biofilms could attain 40.08 %; at a concentration of 800 μg/mL, the disruption rate of VOIMBr-CD on the formed S. aureus biofilms could reach 55.20 % (
                           Fig. S10
                        ). The ability of VOIMBr-CD to disrupt the formed biofilms is relatively weak, which might be attributed to the rather poor dispersibility of VOIMBr-CD in LB medium, thereby not allowing the antibacterial effect to be exerted optimally. In the subsequent studies, considerations should be given to how such a situation can be avoided.
